Former Military Administrator of Kwara State, Salaudeen Latinwo (retd), has backed APC presidential candidate, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu and also expressed his support for the second term bid of Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara State. Latinwo, a retired group captain in the Nigerian Air force, served as Military governor of Kwara State from January 1984 to August 1985. The elder statesman, described as a waste of votes for Nigerians and Kwarans to elect any other candidates as president and governor in the forthcoming general elections. “Tinubu had over the years demonstrated sincerity of purpose, honesty, high level of integrity in governance and endeared himself into the hearts of the people. AbdulRazaq on his part has been a man of high integrity, honesty, hardworking, sagacious and intelligent,” he said.